<paragraph id="186CDF52FFBDB328FF1C7C92CE16FC7E" blockId="2.[151,771,906,933]" box="[151,771,906,933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">
<heading id="4324683EFFBDB328FF1C7C92CE16FC7E" bold="true" box="[151,771,906,933]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="2" pageNumber="548" reason="1">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBDB328FF1C7C92CE16FC7E" bold="true" box="[151,771,906,933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">
Tribe 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBDB328FF697C92CE16FC7E" authority="Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[226,771,906,933]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Platyphyllini">
Platyphyllini 
<bibRefCitation id="7C42A2A3FFBDB328FE007C93CE16FC7E" author="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C." box="[395,771,906,933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548" refId="ref7271" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C. (1895) Monographie der Pseudophylliden. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch- Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien. 45, 282 pp." type="book" year="1895">Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1895</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="50C98CD9FFBDB328FF1C7CCACC90FA8F" pageId="2" pageNumber="548" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="186CDF52FFBDB328FF1C7CCACC90FA8F" blockId="2.[151,1437,978,1365]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBDB328FF1C7CCACC0AFC36" bold="true" box="[151,287,978,1004]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Comments.</emphasis>
This tribe comprises 19 genera and 73 valid species, with a continental distribution between 
<collectingCountry id="60C49FC2FFBDB328FAD37CCBC889FC37" box="[1368,1436,979,1005]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="60C49FC2FFBDB328FF4C7CEFCC0AFBCB" box="[199,287,1015,1041]" name="Mexico" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, and a unique insular and monotypic genus, 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBDB328FC9A7CEFC956FBCB" authority="Beier, 1960" authorityName="Beier" authorityYear="1960" box="[785,1091,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Antillophyllum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBDB328FC9A7CEFCEA2FBCB" box="[785,951,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Antillophyllum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7C42A2A3FFBDB328FC357CEFC956FBCB" author="Beier, M." box="[958,1091,1015,1041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548" pagination="396" refId="ref7013" refString="Beier, M. (1960) Orthoptera Tettigoniidae (Pseudophyllinae II). In: Mertens, R., Hennig, W. &amp; Wermuth, H. (Eds.), Das Tierreich. 74, Walter de Gruyter &amp; Co., Berlin, pp. 396." type="book chapter" year="1960">Beier, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry id="60C49FC2FFBDB328FB007CEFC9F0FBCB" box="[1163,1253,1015,1041]" name="Jamaica" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="7C42A2A3FFBDB328FB7F7CEFCDC6FBEF" author="Cigliano, M. M. &amp; Braun, H. &amp; Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D." pageId="2" pageNumber="548" refId="ref7801" refString="Cigliano, M. M., Braun, H., Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D. (2021) Orthoptera Species File. Version 5.0 / 5.0. Available from: http: // Orthoptera. SpeciesFile. org (accessed 12 June 2021)" type="url" year="2021">
Cigliano 
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBDB328FAD67CEFC89BFBCB" box="[1373,1422,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">et al</emphasis>
., 2021
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBDB328FF637B03CC6CFBEF" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[232,377,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Platyphyllini">Platyphyllini</taxonomicName>
differs from the other tribes by the following characteristics: 
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBDB328FBBD7B02C959FBEE" bold="true" box="[1078,1100,1050,1076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">1.</emphasis>
Anterior margin of pronotum convex and usually projected forward. 
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBDB328FDDB7B26CF70FB82" bold="true" box="[592,613,1086,1112]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">2.</emphasis>
Striae of the mesosternum in a mid-caudal direction, extending from the anterior margin, into the lateral portion of the transverse sulcus, wich is usually long. 
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBDB328FBFC7B7AC999FBA6" bold="true" box="[1143,1164,1122,1148]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">3.</emphasis>
Metafurcal furrow as a groove with paired holes in a widely separated internal process. 
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBDB328FCE47B9ECE90FB7A" bold="true" box="[879,901,1158,1184]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">4.</emphasis>
Costal margin of tegmina uniformly narrowed, anal margin more strongly curved than the costal margin, which is slightly straight. 
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBDB328FBD07BB3C965FB1F" bold="true" box="[1115,1136,1195,1221]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">5.</emphasis>
Main veins frequently indistinct, very fine, and densely reticulated, giving a stippled appearance to the tegmina. 
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBDB328FBFA7BD6C993FB32" bold="true" box="[1137,1158,1230,1256]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">6.</emphasis>
Male terminalia without conspicuous modifications, with some exceptions in some species of 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBDB328FC237BEBC923FAD6" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[936,1078,1267,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Triencentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBDB328FC237BEBC923FAD6" box="[936,1078,1267,1292]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Triencentrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DFD3A4D1FFBDB328FBE57BEBC88DFAD7" authority="Beier, 1960" authorityName="Beier" authorityYear="1960" box="[1134,1432,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Xiphophyllum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBDB328FBE57BEBC81EFAD7" box="[1134,1291,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">Xiphophyllum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7C42A2A3FFBDB328FA987BEBC88DFAD7" author="Beier, M." box="[1299,1432,1267,1293]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548" pagination="396" refId="ref7013" refString="Beier, M. (1960) Orthoptera Tettigoniidae (Pseudophyllinae II). In: Mertens, R., Hennig, W. &amp; Wermuth, H. (Eds.), Das Tierreich. 74, Walter de Gruyter &amp; Co., Berlin, pp. 396." type="book chapter" year="1960">Beier, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="2AA70340FFBDB328FF1C7A0FCDB8FAEB" bold="true" box="[151,173,1303,1329]" pageId="2" pageNumber="548">7.</emphasis>
Ovipositor as long as hind femur or longer, wide, usually straight or slightly curved, and with some denticulations on the dorsal margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
